milestones.description: Rod Marsh and Geoff Lawson's 46-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 33 between Geoff Dymock and Kim Hughes
Rod Marsh has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (3) in ODIs for AUS, going past Ian Chappell's 2
Lance Cairns has become the top wicket-taker for NZ in ODIs with 23 wickets, going past Dayle Hadlee's 20
Hadlee has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (19) for NZ, going past Glenn Turner
Bracewell has broken the record for most catches in an innings (4) in ODIs, going past Tony Greig's 3
